The user updates his self-description as follows: I now especially enjoy polished, hook‑first synth‑pop productions with bright, well‑designed digital synth textures, tight rhythmic programming and glossy, contemporary mastering that keeps lead vocals front and present (think cohesive pop LPs like 1989). I value punchy, compressed pop drums, melodic layering of synths and backing vocals, and album sequencing that rewards front‑to‑back listening while remaining radio‑ready. 
