- Why I would reject if forced to pick the opposite: If there were a second candidate that was more analogue‑warm, piano‑led, and lightly compressed with preserved micro‑dynamics, I would prefer that instead. The Roxette compilation’s glossy mastering and punchy compression are the main reasons it is not an ideal match, but among the attributes provided, the alignment on vocal placement, midrange emphasis, harmonic layering, and sequencing outweighs the production style conflicts.
